author: Nicole Friedman
title: Gas Prices Slip on Supply Concerns
text:
NEW YORK--Natural gas prices slipped Friday from a one-week high as traders assessed the oversupplied market.
Prices rose Thursday after weekly inventory data showed a smaller-than-expected increase in stockpiles, but supplies are still higher than is typical for this time of year.
